      "question": "If the $n^{th}$ term of an Arithmetic Progression is given by $a_n = 4n - 7$, then the value of $a_{15} - a_{10}$ is:",
      "answer": "(A)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Identify the formula for the $n^{th}$ term: $a_n = 4n - 7$.",
          "Calculate the 15th term by substituting $n = 15$: $a_{15} = 4(15) - 7 = 60 - 7 = 53$.",
          "Calculate the 10th term by substituting $n = 10$: $a_{10} = 4(10) - 7 = 40 - 7 = 33$.",
          "Find the difference: $a_{15} - a_{10} = 53 - 33 = 20$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$a_n = 4n - 7 \\\\ a_{15} = 4(15) - 7 = 60 - 7 = 53 \\\\ a_{10} = 4(10) - 7 = 40 - 7 = 33 \\\\ a_{15} - a_{10} = 53 - 33 = 20$"
      },
